column6:
I read somewhere (~~forgive me, but I cannot find a source at the moment. Every time I look it's just stuff on current wildfires or Trump~~) that part of the problem for the wildfires is that California changed how they clear out the forest. It used to be they'd clear out some of the dead underbrush, but a law passed and it considered that tampering with the environment (or something), so they stopped, leaving the underbrush as ready made tinder for the next spark to come along.

&amp;#x200B;

Ah-ha! Found a source. [https://www.americanthinker.com/articles/2018/01/how\_regulations\_made\_californias\_fires\_worse.html](https://www.americanthinker.com/articles/2018/01/how_regulations_made_californias_fires_worse.html) Take it with a grain of salt, as with all sources, but it makes its case well.
